laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild linear atelectasis at the right lung base, moderate-to-large amount of inflammatory stranding in the upper abdomen centered around the pancreas, trace amount of fluid around the free edge of the liver, pancreas relatively fatty and atrophic, multiple bilateral renal cystic lesions measuring up to 8.7 cm in the left kidney, urinary bladder moderately distended with fluid, prostate moderately enlarged, diffuse atherosclerotic calcification of the abdominal aorta.
